04:14.187 --> 04:15.787
Ben Layton?

04:15.788 --> 04:18.423
Just get you to sign
right there, please.

04:20.226 --> 04:22.428
Okay...

04:24.130 --> 04:26.131
Are you okay, man?

04:26.132 --> 04:27.667
I've been worse.

04:35.241 --> 04:37.309
Buddy!

04:37.310 --> 04:38.511
Hey!

04:44.284 --> 04:48.187
Hello!

05:01.301 --> 05:04.403
Ben!

05:04.404 --> 05:08.807
Ben...

05:08.808 --> 05:11.777
Ben... can you tell me
how you're feeling?

05:11.778 --> 05:14.413
That's kind of a personal
question, don't you think?

05:14.414 --> 05:18.317
I know you think you're being
funny but you're just not.

05:18.318 --> 05:20.019
The puppet thinks I'm hilarious.

05:22.488 --> 05:24.323
I think you're avoiding
the real problem.

05:24.324 --> 05:27.492
What do you want me to say?

05:27.493 --> 05:29.361
I... I hit a rough patch
but now I'm better.

05:29.362 --> 05:31.496
It's only been six months
and what did we say

05:31.497 --> 05:33.165
about definitive statements?

05:33.166 --> 05:35.701
You know I started
making this collage?

05:35.702 --> 05:38.770
It's about my past,
about my parents,

05:38.771 --> 05:41.206
me being an only child...

05:41.207 --> 05:45.510
meeting Claire, losing Claire...

05:45.511 --> 05:47.379
I made it out of string.

05:47.380 --> 05:50.349
It's very tactile.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.217
And why are you doing this?

05:52.218 --> 05:55.287
Oh, just trying to figure out
where my life went wrong.

05:55.288 --> 05:59.324
Can I ask you a question?

05:59.325 --> 06:01.226
Do you like yourself?

06:01.227 --> 06:04.496
What, as a friend?

06:04.497 --> 06:12.497
Or... more of a...
friend with benefits?

06:12.839 --> 06:16.375
Ben... I'm a child psychologist.

06:16.376 --> 06:19.379
You shouldn't even be in here.

06:24.417 --> 06:26.551
You're on my hour, Layton.

06:26.552 --> 06:27.353
Okay, just...

06:27.354 --> 06:28.420
Hi there, Alexa.

06:28.421 --> 06:30.021
Are your parents still
getting divorced?

06:30.022 --> 06:32.422
I don't know, is that guy still
having sex with your ex-wife?

06:32.446 --> 06:34.559
How did you know that?

06:34.560 --> 06:35.560
Everybody knows.

06:35.561 --> 06:37.262
Braden F said you're a cry-baby.

06:37.263 --> 06:38.764
Well Braden F wets the bed.

06:38.765 --> 06:40.499
Are you going to trust
whatever he says?

06:40.500 --> 06:41.334
You're a cry-baby.

06:41.335 --> 06:42.335
How do you like that?

06:42.336 --> 06:43.336
Okay, that's enough!

06:43.336 --> 06:44.270
Everyone, just...

06:44.271 --> 06:45.704
Yeah, you'd better run.

06:45.705 --> 06:48.373
Does this look like
running to you?

06:48.374 --> 06:50.242
Does this?

06:50.243 --> 06:53.345
I'm walking away 'cause
I have things to do.

06:53.346 --> 06:55.415
♪

07:35.388 --> 07:36.455
Who does that?

07:36.456 --> 07:37.656
Shoot.

07:37.657 --> 07:38.458
Uh..

07:38.459 --> 07:39.925
What, what'd you say?

07:39.926 --> 07:41.660
What kind of narcissist
wears a shirt

07:41.661 --> 07:44.496
with their own picture on it?

07:44.497 --> 07:47.332
Oh, uh... yeah I, I
bought this at a store.

07:47.333 --> 07:48.400
It's, it's not me.

07:48.401 --> 07:50.302
Mmm, it really is.

07:50.303 --> 07:54.339
It's like a weird, colorful
little version of you.

07:54.340 --> 07:56.608
Self portrait of a man named...?

07:56.609 --> 07:59.978
Ben Layton.

07:59.979 --> 08:01.513
Ben.

08:01.514 --> 08:04.983
Yeah.

08:04.984 --> 08:06.351
You don't get migraines, do you?

08:06.352 --> 08:07.686
No.

08:07.687 --> 08:08.921
No Imitrex, no Migard, I know.

08:12.692 --> 08:15.927
It's, uh... it's for
a skin condition.

08:15.928 --> 08:18.663
Mmm, I got that same condition.

08:18.664 --> 08:21.032
It's a real bitch
around the holidays.

08:21.033 --> 08:25.637
You should take my number.

08:25.638 --> 08:27.472
Paper?

08:27.473 --> 08:31.344
Uh... okay.

08:36.682 --> 08:38.015
You have messy handwriting.

08:38.017 --> 08:39.049
Tough shit.

08:39.051 --> 08:40.586
You should call me.

08:45.358 --> 08:46.825
Cash or credit?

08:46.826 --> 08:52.865
Uh... cash.

09:43.516 --> 09:44.516
Don't be mad.

09:44.517 --> 09:46.351
- Oh, geez!
- I got bored.

09:46.352 --> 09:48.520
Tabby, what the hell,
what are you doing here?

09:48.521 --> 09:49.688
I'm cleaning.

09:49.689 --> 09:51.423
I'm being a good neighbor.

09:51.424 --> 09:52.557
You're welcome!

09:52.558 --> 09:53.678
Did you throw out my plants?

09:53.702 --> 09:54.960
They were dying.

09:54.961 --> 09:57.429
Well, we're all dying.

09:57.430 --> 09:59.631
Usually when I do this
you don't even notice.

09:59.632 --> 10:01.099
I'm pretty stealthy.

10:01.100 --> 10:03.568
I think I need my spare
key back from you.

10:03.569 --> 10:05.437
Well, I disagree.

10:05.438 --> 10:07.739
Okay... all right.

10:07.740 --> 10:10.642
By the way, uh... what is this?

10:10.643 --> 10:11.611
I hate it.

10:11.612 --> 10:13.445
Oh, thank you so much.

10:13.446 --> 10:16.581
Uh... that is my life.

10:16.582 --> 10:19.484
So I guess you kind
of hate my life,

10:19.485 --> 10:21.453
that makes two of us.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.755
I decided to lay
it out visually,

10:23.756 --> 10:27.659
you know so I can see
what went wrong.

10:27.660 --> 10:28.628
Can I just...?

10:28.629 --> 10:30.161
No, no, no, no, no, no...

10:30.162 --> 10:31.963
But it's a mess.

10:31.964 --> 10:35.467
Yeah, I know.

10:35.468 --> 10:38.837
I've been reading some books
about parallel universes,

10:38.838 --> 10:42.774
quantum physics, stuff like
that and how every choice

10:42.775 --> 10:46.811
we make creates thousands
of universes spreading

10:46.812 --> 10:51.683
throughout time and space.

10:51.684 --> 10:55.487
Okay, uh, well let me
give you an example.

10:55.488 --> 10:56.788
Okay. So...

10:56.789 --> 11:01.159
let's say that this
line here is my life,

11:01.160 --> 11:02.827
what was supposed to be my life.

11:02.828 --> 11:05.497
Like, it's quiet, it's
peaceful, it's serene,

11:05.498 --> 11:09.668
it's happy... and then
something happened here.

11:09.669 --> 11:13.772
And now my life is on
this alternate reality

11:13.773 --> 11:16.875
which is shit and I can't
come back from it at all.

11:16.876 --> 11:21.513
So, if I just figure
what this is...

11:21.514 --> 11:23.582
well, then hopefully
I can fix it.

11:25.518 --> 11:26.985
That's permanent
marker, you know?

11:26.986 --> 11:29.922
That's not coming out.

11:33.826 --> 11:35.794
What?

11:35.795 --> 11:38.830
God damnit... is all of it?

11:38.831 --> 11:41.067
Shit.

11:58.217 --> 12:00.919
Hello?

12:00.920 --> 12:02.687
Yes, this is his son.

12:02.688 --> 12:05.624
Who's this?

12:10.564 --> 12:11.564
He's not dead.

12:11.565 --> 12:13.666
Are you sure?

12:17.571 --> 12:18.571
Where am I?

12:18.572 --> 12:20.105
Sir, you've had a heart attack.

12:20.106 --> 12:22.774
Don't tell my son, he's
not good in a crisis.

12:22.775 --> 12:24.175
Dad I'm here, it's me.

12:24.176 --> 12:27.011
Good, listen...

12:27.012 --> 12:28.947
I have to tell you
something in case I die.

12:28.948 --> 12:31.068
You're, you're not going to
die, I don't think, right?

12:31.092 --> 12:31.683
Is he?

12:31.684 --> 12:33.918
Oh, he'll be fine probably.

12:33.919 --> 12:35.854
Just shut up for one minute.

12:35.855 --> 12:37.021
It's about your sister.

12:37.022 --> 12:38.022
Dad, I don't have
a sister, okay?

12:38.023 --> 12:39.023
I'm an only child.

12:39.024 --> 12:40.304
How many drugs did you give him?

12:40.328 --> 12:41.926
No, we didn't give
him any drugs.

12:41.927 --> 12:44.796
Okay, well... well
maybe, should you?

12:44.797 --> 12:46.117
I mean he just had
a heart attack.

12:46.118 --> 12:47.438
Do you want to be
the doctor here?

12:47.462 --> 12:48.933
- No, no, no...
- Ben...

12:48.934 --> 12:55.774
before you were born, your
mother and I, we... adopted.

12:55.775 --> 12:57.055
Then after it went
through, well,

12:57.079 --> 12:59.744
your mother discovered
that she was pregnant.

12:59.745 --> 13:03.281
So, so... we had to
give up the freebie.

13:03.282 --> 13:07.652
So... I almost had a sister?

13:07.653 --> 13:08.653
Are you sure?

13:08.654 --> 13:10.155
Yeah, yes I'm sure.

13:10.156 --> 13:13.091
I held this baby in my arms
and she was cuter than you!

13:13.092 --> 13:15.160
All right, irrelevant, but yeah...
okay.

13:15.161 --> 13:18.129
Ben... she's out
there somewhere.

13:18.130 --> 13:19.799
Just listen to me, damnit.

13:21.967 --> 13:25.069
Ben, she's still out there!

13:25.070 --> 13:29.007
Uh... okay, uh...
what do I do now?

13:29.008 --> 13:33.212
Just go home, we'll call you
after his surgery... probably.

13:45.124 --> 13:47.926
Well, of course we
applied for adoption!

13:47.927 --> 13:49.694
From what the doctors say,

13:49.695 --> 13:52.130
my uterus is pretty
much a death trap.

13:52.131 --> 13:55.834
Besides, I wasn't getting any
younger so it made sense.

13:55.835 --> 13:58.336
Okay, then what happened?

13:58.337 --> 14:01.840
Well... found out I was up
the duff on the same day

14:01.841 --> 14:04.108
they brought the baby.

14:04.109 --> 14:06.878
You can't adopt if you've
got one in the oven.

14:06.879 --> 14:11.015
So... if you'd got the baby home
a little bit sooner or found out

14:11.016 --> 14:12.951
you were pregnant a
little bit later...

14:12.952 --> 14:15.887
You would have had a sister.

14:15.888 --> 14:18.723
Even had a name
picked out for her.

14:18.724 --> 14:23.194
Would've called her
Wendy, after my mother.

14:23.195 --> 14:26.899
Wait... I thought this
was a picture of me.

14:30.736 --> 14:33.338
Okay, uh... so, uh...

14:33.339 --> 14:35.039
what happened to the baby?

14:35.040 --> 14:40.378
Beats me, probably shipped her
off to some other family.

14:40.379 --> 14:42.714
So, she's really out there...

14:42.715 --> 14:43.955
with this whole different life.

14:43.979 --> 14:45.219
She doesn't even know about me,

14:45.243 --> 14:47.819
she doesn't even really
know about herself!

14:47.820 --> 14:48.853
Benny?

14:48.854 --> 14:50.021
What's this all about?

14:50.022 --> 14:51.723
I could've almost had a sister,

14:51.724 --> 14:53.424
do you know how
formative that is?

14:53.425 --> 14:55.226
I'm going to find this girl

14:55.227 --> 14:56.667
and I'm going to see
what she's like,

14:56.668 --> 14:58.228
I've got to know what
I've been missing.

14:58.252 --> 14:59.264
But... I don't know,

14:59.265 --> 15:00.932
it's never a good
idea to mess around

15:00.933 --> 15:02.934
in someone else's past.

15:02.935 --> 15:06.204
Well... good thing for someone
else, this is my past

15:06.205 --> 15:09.774
and I'm going to mess
around with it just fine.

15:09.775 --> 15:12.978
And also, you should call Dad,
he almost died this morning.

15:14.914 --> 15:16.281
Again?

15:16.282 --> 15:18.350
♪

16:04.430 --> 16:06.064
Tabby?

16:06.065 --> 16:07.966
Hey, is uh, is Tabby here?

16:07.967 --> 16:09.400
Tabby?

16:09.401 --> 16:11.069
That guy is here, the
one that looks like

16:11.070 --> 16:13.905
a sad cartoon carrot.

16:13.906 --> 16:16.074
Uh... That doesn't
even make any sense.

16:16.075 --> 16:19.077
Uh, yeah... Tabby look, look...

16:19.078 --> 16:20.144
my whole life is a lie.

16:20.145 --> 16:21.479
I'm sure that's not the case.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.014
It is.

16:23.015 --> 16:25.083
My parent's were going
to adopt, but didn't.

16:25.084 --> 16:26.084
I almost had a sister!

16:26.085 --> 16:29.454
I need you to help me.

16:29.455 --> 16:31.189
Okay, but I'm at work right now.

16:31.190 --> 16:32.824
Yeah, we're going to leave here.

16:32.825 --> 16:35.293
Okay, we're going to go break
into an adoption agency

16:35.294 --> 16:37.028
and we're going to
steal a bunch of files

16:37.029 --> 16:41.966
and figure out who this girl is
and see if she can fix my life.

16:41.967 --> 16:43.201
What the fuck?

16:43.202 --> 16:44.482
We are not breaking
the law, Ben!

16:44.506 --> 16:45.837
Ow, why are you hitting me?

16:45.838 --> 16:47.105
Because you're being an idiot.

16:47.106 --> 16:49.440
This here, is not
rational behavior.

16:49.441 --> 16:51.042
No, no, no, it's very rational.

16:51.043 --> 16:52.110
Okay?

16:52.111 --> 16:53.845
This is the only
thing that's left.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.013
This is the thing.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.115
I find her, right...

16:57.116 --> 17:00.051
and then I can figure out
where my life went wrong...

17:00.052 --> 17:02.987
and hopefully
correct everything.

17:02.988 --> 17:04.468
And what if you don't
like the answer?

17:04.492 --> 17:06.858
Then at least I tried.

17:06.858 --> 17:08.059
At least I tried.

17:08.060 --> 17:11.296
Tabby, I am running
out of options here.

17:15.401 --> 17:16.901
Okay.

17:16.902 --> 17:19.237
Fine, uh... if this
is what you need

17:19.238 --> 17:20.039
then I guess I can
help a little.

17:20.040 --> 17:22.040
This is what I need.

17:22.040 --> 17:23.320
But we are not breaking the law.

17:23.345 --> 17:24.042
Okay.

17:24.044 --> 17:25.324
And we're not stealing anything.

17:25.348 --> 17:26.176
Sure.

17:26.178 --> 17:27.345
And you have to promise me

17:27.346 --> 17:28.866
that things are not
going to get weird.

17:28.890 --> 17:30.826
You know I can't
promise you that.

17:32.151 --> 17:33.184
Yeah, I guess.

17:33.185 --> 17:34.286
Yeah... it's already weird.

17:35.988 --> 17:37.889
This all makes sense.

17:37.890 --> 17:41.359
My parents were married for like...
seven years before me.

17:41.360 --> 17:43.194
They probably thought
they'd never have a kid.

17:43.195 --> 17:45.396
Of course they tried
to adopt, of course!

17:45.397 --> 17:46.697
What does it matter?

17:46.698 --> 17:48.533
Your parents adopted a
baby and gave her back.

17:48.534 --> 17:49.934
What does it have
to do with you?

17:49.935 --> 17:51.369
Uh... I don't know Tabby,

17:51.370 --> 17:53.410
maybe because she could've
taught me so many things.

17:53.434 --> 17:55.273
She could've taught me
how to talk to girls

17:55.274 --> 17:56.407
and cool dance moves.

17:56.408 --> 17:57.708
You hate dancing,

17:57.709 --> 17:59.944
it's one of the five
things we have in common.

17:59.945 --> 18:03.014
Yeah, well maybe I would've loved
dancing if I had a sister.

18:03.015 --> 18:05.296
God, I could've learned a trade
skill and lived in a house

18:05.297 --> 18:07.377
with a kid and a wife who
likes to show her cleavage.

18:07.401 --> 18:08.286
Eww!

18:08.287 --> 18:10.122
Top of the tits, Tabby.

18:13.225 --> 18:14.358
This is never going to work.

18:14.359 --> 18:16.194
Okay, that guy's not
going to help us.

18:16.195 --> 18:17.428
No, we're already here.

18:17.429 --> 18:19.063
This was your idea.

18:19.064 --> 18:21.032
Okay... What can I do for you?

18:21.033 --> 18:22.266
Hi there, uh...

18:22.267 --> 18:25.103
well we're looking for the
adoption records of a girl

18:25.104 --> 18:28.606
that was born, uh,
30 years ago and...

18:28.607 --> 18:29.874
we don't have her name

18:29.875 --> 18:32.110
but we do have the name
of the people who, uh,

18:32.111 --> 18:33.979
didn't adopt her.

18:35.214 --> 18:36.447
Uh, you also have a photo.

18:36.448 --> 18:40.018
Oh yeah, I have a... photo.

18:42.654 --> 18:45.256
Okay... my parents had to give
her back when they found out

18:45.257 --> 18:47.425
they were going to have
me and I'm just...

18:47.426 --> 18:50.261
trying to track her
down so I can know

18:50.262 --> 18:52.964
what my life would've been
like if I had a sister.

18:52.965 --> 18:57.301
So, uh... you want me to hand
over the adoption records

18:57.302 --> 18:59.237
of a stranger...

18:59.238 --> 19:03.141
um, because you're having some
kind of emotional crisis?

19:03.142 --> 19:05.176
Basically... yes.

19:05.177 --> 19:06.177
It's a quest.

19:06.178 --> 19:07.745
Yeah, it's a quest.

19:07.746 --> 19:12.984
Okay, there is literally no way
that that's going to happen.

19:12.985 --> 19:15.220
What if I gave you $50?

19:16.155 --> 19:18.089
I'm going to need
your parents names

19:18.090 --> 19:19.250
and the date of the adoption.

19:19.274 --> 19:20.458
Yeah, got it.

19:20.459 --> 19:25.129
That's also... that's
what I also have.

19:25.130 --> 19:25.998
I will be right back. Stay here.

19:25.999 --> 19:27.065
Yeah.

19:30.269 --> 19:32.203
Whoa, okay.

19:32.204 --> 19:35.606
Okay, uh, I need to borrow
50 bucks right now.

19:35.607 --> 19:36.707
Are you serious?

19:36.708 --> 19:38.643
Mmm.

19:38.644 --> 19:40.011
Okay, you have to pay me back.

19:40.012 --> 19:42.213
- Fine.
- Yeah, 'cause it's $50.

19:42.214 --> 19:43.214
Sure.

19:43.215 --> 19:45.083
Damn, I'm good for it.

19:50.622 --> 19:52.390
I had to go to the archives...

19:52.391 --> 19:54.192
Okay, well regardless
I appreciate it,

19:54.193 --> 19:55.326
thank you so much.

19:55.327 --> 19:57.327
This means a lot, I mean
you're a good man, really.

19:57.351 --> 19:59.063
Not really.

19:59.064 --> 20:00.731
I hate this place.

20:00.732 --> 20:01.700
Okay, thank you.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.134
Right on, thank you so much.

20:03.135 --> 20:04.303
Thank you.

20:43.375 --> 20:45.244
Hey... Ben.

20:48.714 --> 20:51.782
You know this isn't going
to make you happy, right?

20:51.783 --> 20:52.783
I know what I'm doing.

20:52.784 --> 20:55.286
You do?

20:55.287 --> 20:57.588
You're wearing a button
down shirt inside out.

20:57.589 --> 21:02.426
Looks to me like you
don't know shit.

21:02.427 --> 21:05.330
Well, what do you know?

21:42.301 --> 21:43.334
